# WME OpenMaps (Candy Remix)

A modernized, performance-focused fork of the original [WME OpenMaps](https://github.com/Glodenox/wme-om) script by Tom 'Glodenox' Puttemans. 

This userscript augments the [Waze Map Editor](https://www.waze.com/editor) by allowing editors to overlay external, open-data maps (such as local cadasters, high-resolution orthophotos, and administrative boundaries) directly onto the editing canvas.

The **Candy Remix** focuses on aligning the script with modern WME SDK standards, improving UI/UX density, and adding advanced cartographic tools for power editors.

## Key Features

* **Advanced Visual Adjustments:** Take full control of how layers render with native CSS blend modes (Multiply, Screen, Overlay, etc.), alongside real-time sliders for Opacity, Brightness, Contrast, Saturation, and Gamma.
* **Modernized UI:** A rebuilt sidebar interface featuring clean metadata headers, easily comparable monospace bounding boxes, and compact avatar badges with regional flags.
* **WME SDK Native:** Rewritten to utilize the official Waze Map Editor SDK, ensuring maximum stability and future-proofing against internal Waze rendering updates.
* **Asynchronous Engine:** Map layer state synchronization is handled asynchronously so the editor stays responsive. Per-map **Source & Waze** links Waze’s [Map Data Attribution](https://support.google.com/waze/answer/12075833) guidance and an optional prefilled [layer request form](https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSckKm-9hDRALxD2qhngvffzFppOS9C8FDD2w8yuiIE0En8Q8A/viewform); provider terms are informational only and do not lock layers.

## Installation

1. Ensure you have a userscript manager extension installed in your browser (such as [Tampermonkey](https://www.tampermonkey.net/)).
2. **[Click here to install WME OpenMaps (Candy Remix)](#)** *(Note: Insert your GreasyFork/GitHub raw link here)*.
3. Refresh the Waze Map Editor. The OpenMaps tab () will automatically appear in the left sidebar.

## Changelog

### 2026.04.12

- **Developer mode & Waze `not_listed` gating:** Seven quick taps on the **Active maps** title (within a few seconds) enables persisted **developer mode**. Catalog maps whose **Source & Waze** accreditation is **Not on Waze list** are hidden from **Maps to add** by default and cannot be added until developer mode is on. Turning developer mode off **locks** any such rows already in **Active maps** (lock icon, Waze layer menu checkbox disabled, sub-layer eyes disabled) until developer mode is on again. **Exit developer mode** is in the OpenMaps sidebar footer next to the help toggle.
- **2026.04.12.2 — Session “I agree”:** With developer mode, those catalog maps can be added but stay off the canvas until **I agree** under **Source & Waze** (per session; cleared when developer mode turns off). A **Not Accredited** tag on the row opens that panel; the summary pill uses the same label; Waze accreditation copy and exit-developer confirm text were updated accordingly.
- **2026.04.12.3 — I agree unlock + tag:** **I agree** now triggers a visible unlock: the gate calls the real in-panel **rebuild map layers** helper (it was previously out of scope from `applyWazeNotListedGate`, so layer UI stayed wrong). Consent is keyed by **`mapId`** with numeric/string parity; **I agree** is a native button with an immediate + deferred gate refresh. **Not Accredited** is an inline compact pill next to the title and hides after session agreement for that map.

### 2026.04.11

- **Waze accreditation workflow:** Replaced mandatory in-script **Terms of Use** acceptance with a per-map **Source & Waze** section. **Provider terms** are optional informational links when the catalog defines a `touId`. **Waze** box shows accreditation status (vs [Map Data Attribution](https://support.google.com/waze/answer/12075833)), a link to that help page, and a prefilled [Open Source Data Layer Request](https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSckKm-9hDRALxD2qhngvffzFppOS9C8FDD2w8yuiIE0En8Q8A/viewform) URL. Status for built-in layers comes from `OPEN_MAPS_WAZE_ACCREDITATION_BY_ATTRIBUTION` (see `OPENMAPS_WAZE_ATTRIBUTION_VERIFICATION.md`). Removed ToU lock on the visibility control, sidebar ToU notice, **ToU pending** active-maps filter, **Revoke all terms** control, and background ToU fetch/revoke logic.
- **Source & Waze polish (2026.04.11.2):** Google Form **editor name** prefill resolves the logged-in user from page **`W.loginManager`** (including Backbone-style models) and the script’s WME **SDK** instance; the **Waze** panel uses the same background/border palette as the accreditation pill; **Not on Waze list** copy explains practical limits on treating the overlay as a Waze-approved map source in WME.

### 2026.04.08

- **Map Feature Styles:** "Use layer-specific styles" under **Map layers** toggles per-sublayer colors and ring-in-round symbols for **ESRI_FEATURE**, **KML / My Maps**, **WMS**, and **ArcGIS MapServer (ESRI)** rows; state persists in `saveMapState`. ESRI_FEATURE click uses the same layer key as Map Inspector.
- **KML map clicks:** KML vector layers are included in the document-capture hit-test (they only had `openMapsEsriAvatarFill` on FeatureServer layers before). Stable ids use the `kml_<folder>` segment so list selection matches map clicks; inner-ring OL features resolve to the outer placemark for hit-testing.
- **Symbol parity:** Shared inner-ring ratio (`OPENMAPS_POINT_INNER_RADIUS_FRAC` = 0.75) for Map Inspector list dots, map points, and hover/select lift symbols; ESRI_FEATURE highlights show map-colored outer + layer-hash inner when the option is on; KML highlights respect the checkbox for points and line strokes.
- **KML inner color (2026.04.08.3):** Map point inner rings and line/polygon strokes use the same resolved folder color as the inspector list — prefer **`openMapsKmlColorHex`** from parsed KML **Style** when present, otherwise the title+folder hash (`openMapsKmlResolvedFolderFillHex`).

### 2026.04.07

- **Map layers:** Sub-layer list shows summary counts `(visible/total)` in the header. Added an actions menu (`⋮`) next to the Map layers header with **Show all layers** and **Hide all layers** shortcuts.
- **KML parser fix:** Uploaded KML (including Google My Maps export stubs that resolve to real KML) now transforms coordinates to WME’s actual map projection (`EPSG:900913`) so points/features render and become discoverable in Map Inspector.
- **KML / My Maps viewport:** `LOCAL_KML` and `GOOGLE_MY_MAPS` overlays are no longer marked out-of-viewport in a way that blocked KML fetch and left only the placeholder **KML** sub-layer; folder sub-layers merge from the KML tree when needed, and **BBox** is derived from loaded geometry (persisted for uploads).
- **KML draw path (OpenLayers 2):** Per-feature styles are now passed through `drawFeature` so Canvas/SVG actually paint markers (the layer StyleMap stays a no-op shell on purpose).
- **KML / My Maps (2026.04.07.5):** Parsed **folder sub-layers** persist into **Your maps** (`layers` / `default_layers` with bbox) so the sidebar stays aligned after reload; each KML apply ends with **`updateLayers`** so the vector and Map Inspector resync immediately. **Map layers** sidebar rebuild retries when the sub-layer DOM is not ready yet; **Canvas/SVG** renderer `drawFeature` hooks forward **`feature.style`** for OpenMaps KML layer names when rendering bypasses `Layer.drawFeature`.
- **KML first paint (2026.04.07.6):** Per-feature symbolizers are set **before** `addFeatures` so OpenLayers 2 Canvas/SVG does not draw only from the invisible layer **StyleMap** on the first pass (empty map + empty Map Inspector viewport). Renderer hooks also read **`this.layer`** when **`feature.layer`** is not attached yet.
- **KML + Map Inspector (2026.04.07.7):** GMM diagnostic logging reports **OpenLayers on-layer** feature counts (the old line mirrored **parsed** placemark count only). **Folder headers** show **in view / loaded** totals from the KML master list. Viewport indexing uses a **fallback map extent** when `getMapExtent()` is null so KML rows can still populate; with **`openmaps-kml-diag`**, logs can flag **zero viewport intersection** with a bounds sample. **`updateLayers`** reapplies folder styles if the vector layer is empty while **`__openmapsKmlMasterFeatures`** still has data (e.g. after layer recreate).
- **I18n (2026.04.07.8):** **French** and **Portuguese (Brazil)** translations for the Map Inspector KML folder **in view / loaded** label (`inspector_kml_folder_feature_counts`).
- **KML OL layer + Map Inspector (2026.04.07.9):** Placemarks on the OpenLayers vector are **clones** of **`__openmapsKmlMasterFeatures`** so removing/clearing the OL layer cannot corrupt templates needed for the next paint. **Legacy `main` sub-layer:** when real KML folder rows replace the old single **main** row, new folders default **on** so a hidden **main** no longer forces **zero** visible sub-layers (which tore down the vector and left MI at **0 in view**). Map Inspector can list viewport hits from **master** geometry when the OL layer is still empty but the map row should draw.
- **KML `MapHandle.map` (2026.04.07.10):** Each map row now sets **`this.map`** to the map definition object. KML **`openMapsApplyKmlFolderFeatureStyles`** and related code read **`mapHandle.map`**; it was never assigned, so apply always exited early (**`hasMap: false`** in KML diag) and the OL layer stayed empty despite parsed placemarks.

### 2026.04.06

- **Layer UI + KML symbology (v2026.04.06.1):** Map **sub-layer** rows use **neutral text tags** for origin (**Catalog** / **Cloud** / **Unknown**, **Default**, **Upload** for local files, **My Maps** for Google) instead of corner FA badges; layer **title** tooltip is shortened to the same phrases. **KML / My Maps** folders each get a **distinct color** on the map and in the **Map Inspector** (list dots, idle symbols, hover/selection) via `map title + folder id`. When KML defines a placemark **`Icon` href** (http/https), that image is shown in the **layer chip** (fallback to initials on error).
- **Map Inspector folders + sidebar sync (v2026.04.06.2–.3):** Under each map, **folder checkboxes** only **expand/collapse** nested feature rows; **which layers participate in viewport scans** stays in the map **⋮** menu. **Enabled** Active Maps sub-layers always show as folder headers with **(0)** when empty. **Sidebar** sub-layer toggles call the inspector API so the **viewport list rescans**; **KML** source-tree updates also **clear the viewport cache** before refresh.
- **Map layers row layout (v2026.04.06.4):** In **Map layers**, origin **tags** moved to a **second line under the layer title** so names get the width between avatar and actions and pills show **full text** instead of cramped ellipsis.
- **Upload KML visibility (v2026.04.06.5):** Toggling the map **off then on** no longer leaves uploaded KML **empty** (map + Map Inspector) until refresh — the “fetch already triggered” latch is set only after OpenLayers visibility checks pass.
- **Sidebar map eye + Map Inspector (v2026.04.06.6):** The main **show/hide** control now runs **`updateLayers`** so the **Map Inspector** feature list and **viewport scan** immediately reflect the map (and its sub-layers) being on or off.
- **KML reload latch (v2026.04.06.7):** After **hide/show** (or turning the last **Map layers** folder off), KML/My Maps vectors could stay **empty** because the script still thought a load had finished. The fetch latch now **resets when the layer is hidden** (and on **HTTP errors**) so geometry and Map Inspector repopulate.
- **Map layers + Map Inspector (v2026.04.06.8):** Inspector **`notifyHandlesChanged`** now runs **`runViewportIndex(true)`** immediately (and clears the move debounce timer), so **Map layers** eye toggles refresh the inspector **viewport list** in line with map show/hide — not only after a debounced pan/zoom.
- **KML hide + MI folder UI (v2026.04.06.9):** **Map layers** folder **off** now applies a **full invisible** OpenLayers style (not only `display:none`, which OL2 still merged with defaults). Map Inspector **folder headers** are no longer native **`<details>`** rows, so **clicking the title row does not collapse** the section — only the **checkbox** toggles nested rows.
- **KML viewport + MI list (v2026.04.06.10):** **Map Inspector** viewport indexing for **KML / My Maps** now skips placemarks whose **Map layers** folder is **hidden**, matching non-KML vectors — so hidden folders do not keep **feature rows**, counts, or **stale** highlight geometry on the map.
- **Sidebar ↔ MI scan + ESRI_FEATURE (v2026.04.06.11):** Each **Map layers** sub-row **eye** now drives inspector **source inclusion** for that layer (viewport list + ingested query rows), clears **selection/hover** for items in that layer so **child highlight symbols** on the map disappear, and **ArcGIS FeatureServer** maps **reschedule** their bbox fetch when sub-layers change so turning a layer **on** reloads features.
- **KML folder hide on map (v2026.04.06.12–.13):** **Google My Maps / uploaded KML** first used a context **StyleMap**; WME’s **Canvas** renderer still left **ghost graphics** while inspector hit-testing stopped (symbols looked active but were not clickable). **v2026.04.06.13** keeps a **`__openmapsKmlMasterFeatures`** list and **`removeFeatures` / `addFeatures`** by sidebar folder visibility so the OL layer’s feature set matches the map; per-feature `style` plus a **minimal** default StyleMap handles drawing.

### 2026.04.05

- **Your maps (v2026.04.05.1):** **Upload KML** — choose a `.kml` file (plain XML); OpenMaps stores the text in settings, adds it under **Your maps**, and draws it with the same deferred OpenLayers KML path as Google My Maps (no My Maps opt-in required). **KMZ** is not supported. Rough **2 MB** text cap to avoid storage limits.
- **Google My Maps (v2026.04.05.2):** The KML fetch URL now appends **`forcekml=1`**, matching the working pattern from classic [WME Open Other Maps](https://greasyfork.org/en/scripts/32758-wme-open-other-maps) (JustinS83), which can improve reliability of Google’s KML response.
- **Upload KML / NetworkLink (v2026.04.05.3):** Google-style **stub** KML (only a `<NetworkLink>` to e.g. `maps/d/kml?…`) is now resolved by **fetching the linked document** (Tampermonkey); OpenLayers does not load network links from raw XML. **`@connect www.google.com`** added for that request.
- **Google My Maps points + NetworkLink (v2026.04.05.4):** **Placemark** geometry (including **points** under **`<Folder>`**s) is read with a **small DOM-based KML parser** aligned with how classic [WME Open Other Maps](https://greasyfork.org/en/scripts/32758-wme-open-other-maps) uses **`OpenLayers.Format.MyMapKML`**; stock **`OpenLayers.Format.KML`** remains a **fallback** only. **Google My Maps** fetches that return only a **`<NetworkLink>`** stub now **resolve the link** the same way as uploaded KML.
- **KML folders + Map Inspector sources (v2026.04.05.5):** Each KML **`<Folder>`** is a **toggleable sub-layer** in Active Maps (alongside **Not in a folder** for document-level placemarks). **Map Inspector** adds **Layers to inspect** with a checkbox per sub-layer (and **bounds** where applicable) for **WMS, ArcGIS, FeatureServer, Google My Maps, and uploaded KML**, plus **All / None / Match Active Maps layers** to bulk-set which sources participate in viewport scans.
- **Map Inspector layout + KML restore (v2026.04.05.6):** Layer/source checkboxes moved **under each map** inside **Features by map** (expanded map row). **KML / My Maps** no longer triggers the sidebar **“saved layer names removed”** warning when persisted Active Maps lists **folder ids** but the stored map definition still only had **`main`** — those ids are merged into the definition on load.
- **Map Inspector folder tree (v2026.04.05.7):** Under each map, viewport hits are grouped under **collapsible folder headers** (KML folders, WMS/ArcGIS sub-layers, bounds, etc.) with features nested underneath — not a separate flat “layers to inspect” list. **All / None / Match Active Maps layers** for the viewport scan lives in the map row **⋮** menu; each folder header still has a **checkbox** to include or exclude that source from scans.

### 2026.04.04

- **Fix (satellite + Google My Maps, v2026.04.04.1):** Restored **v37-style hook gating** — `syncOpenMapsLayerIndices` no longer installs global OpenLayers **`Layer.setZIndex`** / **`resetLayersZIndex`** hooks on every run (the v40 rollback had put that back), so satellite is not wrapped whenever any OpenMaps row exists. Hooks attach when **`pinOpenMapsOverlayStackTop`** actually pins ESRI/inspector overlays; **`addlayer` / debounced `moveend`** pin listeners register only when **`openMapsOverlayPinStackHasWork()`**. **`minForeignAbove`** for tile stacking now walks **`olMap.layers`** with **resolved OpenLayers refs** so My Maps vectors are not misclassified as foreign when `W.map.getLayers()` uses different object identity than `handles[].layer`.
- **Fix (satellite + Google My Maps, v2026.04.04.2):** Tile stacking math now uses **`olMap.getLayerIndex`** consistently for the **aerial floor** and the **lowest foreign layer above aerial** (avoids mixing `layers[]` enumeration index with stack order). Google My Maps vectors are **`removeLayer`’d** from the map when the row should not display (hidden, no active sub-layer, out of area, or ToU not accepted), not left on the stack as invisible OL layers. KML fetch no longer runs **`syncOpenMapsLayerIndices`** after every load.
- **Diagnostics (Google My Maps, v2026.04.04.3):** Opt-in troubleshooting: set `localStorage.setItem('openmaps-gmm-diag','1')` and reload WME. OpenMaps then logs **`olMap` layer stack** snapshots around sync / GMM map ops / KML load, logs any **`setLayerIndex`** or **`removeLayer`** on **non-OpenMaps** layers, and warns if **`olMap.layers.length`** changes during **`syncOpenMapsLayerIndices`** (to debug native layers such as roads disappearing). Disable with `localStorage.removeItem('openmaps-gmm-diag')` and reload.
- **Fix (satellite + Google My Maps, v2026.04.04.4 - .8):** WME satellite maps turning blank (tile requests dropped/blocked) while roads remain visible indicates the OpenLayers `moveend` event chain or the native Waze map state synchronizer is being broken. OpenMaps now **bypasses WME’s `W.map.addLayer` wrapper entirely** for heavy vector layers (My Maps / ESRI_FEATURE), adding them directly to the underlying OpenLayers engine. This stops WME’s React state from tracking thousands of foreign vectors. Hidden My Maps now also **lazily defer KML fetching and map attachment** until they are checked, preventing rapid attach/detach sequences or blocking `XMLHttpRequest` calls from starving Waze's tile renderer on boot. Event registrations are fully decoupled from Waze's move lifecycle. KML restricts loading to **1500** features maximum.
- **Google My Maps off in build + session cleanup (v2026.04.04.17–.18):** The script ships with **`OPEN_MAPS_FEATURE_GOOGLE_MY_MAPS = false`**. Saved **Active Maps** entries for Google My Maps are **not restored** while integration is off, and one post-boot **`saveMapState`** removes them from persisted active state so they no longer create handles or touch OpenLayers after reload. The Your maps paste row is **disabled** when the feature is hard-retired; My Maps definitions are also hidden from the “add map” suggestion list until integration is enabled. Power users can still force the old path with **`unsafeWindow.__OPEN_MAPS_FORCE_GMM__`** before load plus **`openmaps-enable-google-mymaps`** in `localStorage`.
- **My Maps piece-by-piece rollout (v2026.04.04.19):** Introduces **`OPEN_MAPS_GMM_ROLLOUT_STAGE`**. **Stage 1** sets **`OPEN_MAPS_FEATURE_GOOGLE_MY_MAPS`** back to true so My Maps is no longer hard-retired, while **`openmaps-enable-google-mymaps`** + reload is still required before any KML is restored or drawn; **`openmaps-disable-google-mymaps=1`** still overrides. **Stage 0** restores the previous “off in build” behavior without deleting code.
- **My Maps opt-in copy (v2026.04.04.20):** Banner, Add button, and inactive-card hints pick the message via **`openMapsGoogleMyMapsOptInBlockedMessageKey()`** — with rollout **stage 1**, editors only see the simple localStorage opt-in text (no false **`__OPEN_MAPS_FORCE_GMM__`** requirement). A separate string covers **force-unlock** when the feature is off in the build but **`unsafeWindow.__OPEN_MAPS_FORCE_GMM__`** was set before load.
- **Troubleshooting snapshot (v2026.04.04.21):** Internal **`OPEN_MAPS_VERSION`** matches **`// @version`** again (bridge logs showed stale `.17`). Set **`openmaps-troubleshoot=1`** and reload for a JSON status dump; call **`openMapsPrintTroubleshootStatus("…")`** on the page (exposed on **`unsafeWindow`** when allowed) after reproducing satellite issues. Includes handle counts by type and per–My Map row flags (`touAccepted`, **`hasOlVector`**, sublayers).
- **Troubleshoot clarity (v2026.04.04.22):** Dropped the false **“total vs visible mismatch”** warning (normal for WME). Added **`eligibleForOlVector`** per My Map row, **`handlesWithOpenLayersLayer`**, a plain-language **`satelliteDebugHint`**, and **`noteBridgeVsBody`** when **`GM_info.script.version`** lags a locally injected script.
- **Troubleshoot hints (v2026.04.04.23):** **`satelliteDebugHint`** distinguishes **My Maps saved but not eligible** (hidden / ToU / sublayers / out of area — no KML expected) from **eligible but vector not attached** (load or attach still in play).
- **Troubleshoot zero-layer case (v2026.04.04.24):** When **`handlesWithOpenLayersLayer` is 0**, hints no longer point at “other overlays”; they state that OpenMaps tile sync is inactive and recommend **disabling the userscript** to isolate WME/browser causes. Payload adds **`overlayPinStackHasWork`**.
- **Troubleshoot console alias (v2026.04.04.25):** **`OpenMapsPrintTroubleshootStatus`** is also exposed on **`unsafeWindow`** (same as **`openMapsPrintTroubleshootStatus`**) for case-sensitivity mistakes in the devtools console.
- **Google My Maps teardown (v2026.04.04.26):** When a My Map row stops being drawable (hidden, Terms not accepted, opt-out, or no sub-layer on), the script **destroys** the KML **`OpenLayers.Layer.Vector`** and clears the handle’s **`layer` ref**, not only `removeLayer` from `olMap` — so patched **`moveTo`** and listeners do not linger while the sidebar card remains.
- **GMM diagnostics (v2026.04.04.27):** With **`openmaps-gmm-diag=1`**, heavy console tracing (**`setLayerIndex`** / **`removeLayer`** wraps, stack snapshots) is **gated** until an OpenLayers **layer or bbox** exists or **overlay-pin work** is active, so an inactive My Map row alone does not spam every sync. **Not treated as affecting satellite tile loading** — dev logging only. Payload fields **`gmmDiagHeavyHooksActive`** / **`noteGmmDiag`** (v2026.04.04.28) describe hook state; diag is **ruled out** as a satellite root cause.
- **Satellite investigation payload (v2026.04.04.28):** Opt-in troubleshoot JSON adds **`ruledOutNonSuspects`** and **`satelliteInvestigationHypotheses`** (structured hypotheses and **eliminateIf** hints for elimination runs).
- **Google My Maps restore + sync idle (v2026.04.04.29):** A persisted **Active Maps** row for **Google My Maps** with **Terms not accepted** and **hidden** is **not restored** on load (the map remains under **Your maps**; re-add after accepting Terms). **`syncOpenMapsLayerIndices`** returns early when no handle has an OpenLayers layer and **ESRI / Map Inspector** overlay-pin work is off, skipping repeated **`W.map.getLayers()`** / aerial-floor work during idle sessions.

### 2026.04.03

- **Fix (satellite + Google My Maps, v2026.04.03.34):** With only a My Map (or other vector overlay) active, constant OpenLayers stack re-pinning on every pan/zoom could stop WME satellite imagery from loading. ESRI_FEATURE / My Maps vectors are pinned only when the row is on and the layer is visible; hidden maps no longer re-enter the stack via the layer sweep; pan/zoom re-pin is debounced (~220 ms); overlay z-index rules clear when nothing is pinned; tile stacking also keys off the `satellite_imagery` layer name when `earthengine-legacy` is missing.
- **Fix (satellite + Google My Maps, v2026.04.03.35):** My Maps KML is **excluded** from the ESRI-style overlay pin (top-of-`olMap` index, `!important` z-index, hoisting layer `div`s in the viewport). It is ordered only through **`syncOpenMapsLayerIndices`** above aerial imagery, like tile overlays. The pin stack could still break satellite tiles when My Maps was the sole overlay.
- **Fix (satellite + Google My Maps, v2026.04.03.36):** While a My Map row is **hidden** (or out of area / OL layer not visible), **`syncOpenMapsLayerIndices` no longer calls `setLayerIndex` on that vector** — it remained on the map and was still being reordered. Stacking math uses only participating handles. The **`setZIndex` / `resetLayersZIndex` → overlay stylesheet** path runs only when **ESRI_FEATURE** pin work or **Map Inspector** overlays exist, so satellite layers are not pulled through that pipeline on every pan/zoom when only a hidden My Map sits in Active Maps.
- **Fix (satellite + Google My Maps, v2026.04.03.37):** **`syncOpenMapsLayerIndices` no longer installs** the global OpenLayers **`Layer.setZIndex`** / **`Map.resetLayersZIndex`** hooks on every sync. Those hooks were still attached as soon as any OpenMaps row existed (e.g. a hidden My Map), so **every** WME layer—including satellite—went through our wrapper. Hooks and **`moveend` re-pin** are registered only when **ESRI_FEATURE** pin work or **Map Inspector** overlays need them; **`pinOpenMapsOverlayStackTop`** installs the same hooks the first time it pins a non-empty stack.
- **Fix (satellite + Google My Maps, v2026.04.03.38):** Hidden/out-of-area My Maps are now **fully detached from the map** (`W.map`/`olMap`) instead of staying as invisible vectors. This prevents “My Map present in list” from touching OpenLayers layer state and satellite tile flow. The My Maps vector is recreated only when that row becomes visible again.
- **Hotfix (startup, v2026.04.03.39):** Reverted the `v2026.04.03.38` My Maps detach path after startup regressions. The script keeps `v2026.04.03.37` behavior as stable baseline while satellite/My Maps debugging continues.
- **Hotfix rollback (startup, v2026.04.03.40):** Stepped back one more level to the **v2026.04.03.36 runtime path** (restore hook/`moveend` registration flow from before `v2026.04.03.37`) to recover script startup reliability first.
- **Startup fix (v2026.04.03.41):** In some bridge/Tampermonkey environments, `wme-initialized` appears but `wme-ready` never fires. OpenMaps now keeps the normal `wme-ready` listener **and** sets a guarded fallback timer (single launch) so startup does not stall at “waiting for wme-ready signal…”.
- **Fix (satellite + Google My Maps, v2026.04.03.42):** Google My Maps vectors are **never** passed through `syncOpenMapsLayerIndices` `setLayerIndex` (previously only hidden/out-of-area/invisible rows were skipped). Visible KML was still reordered above aerial on every sync and KML refresh, which could stop satellite tiles after pan/zoom. My Maps stays at the default OpenLayers stack position; tile/WMS/ESRI overlays still sync above aerial.
- **Your maps (Google My Maps):** Paste the **normal browser URL** from Google My Maps while **editing, previewing, or sharing** (e.g. `…/maps/d/edit?mid=…`); you do **not** need a separate “KML link”—OpenMaps reads the `mid` and loads geometry via Tampermonkey. Parser trims stray quotes/punctuation; hash/query fallbacks. Entries persist in `userMaps`; accept **Google’s terms** per map. Same list is intended for future **WMS / ArcGIS / XYZ** custom URLs.
- **WMS (ArcGIS REST):** Map details include a checkbox to turn **REST viewport feature queries** (Map Inspector `/query` traffic) on or off **separately** from WMS tiles. Tiles still follow Active Maps visibility and per-layer toggles; when probe is off, inspector no longer runs those REST requests. Queries are gated by ToU, out-of-area, and whether the map is disabled in Active Maps, and no longer require the WMS tile layer’s OpenLayers visibility (so brief desyncs or missing layer handles are less likely to block `/query` alone).
- **Region Universal (`UN`):** The “draw boundary box on map” control is hidden; saved bbox state is cleared and the bbox vector overlay stays off (world-scale bounds are not useful in the editor).
- **ESRI_FEATURE (FeatureServer vectors):** Map options no longer show the WMS-style transparent checkbox, CSS filter sliders / blend / invert / reset, the pixel-manipulations block, or **opacity**—vectors are always drawn at full opacity in-engine; `applyFilters` already skipped vectors. Non-`UN` maps still get the bbox checkbox when applicable.
- **Map Inspector:** The per-map checkbox in the feature list only **expands or collapses** rows under that map. It no longer toggles Active Maps visibility (the sidebar eye / layer checkbox still controls whether the overlay is on), so collapsing a group no longer disables the map or removes it from the inspector for that reason alone.
- **UI:** Hide the “Search this area” Places pill (**WME React**: `container--*`, `iconContainer--*`, `.w-icon-search`, `div.text` — not Google `.gm-style`) with `:has(...)` CSS and a `div.text` phrase sweep; legacy Google-styled map controls are still hidden where they appear. Sweeps run **immediately** on mutation (plus rAF / debounced follow-up) and again on map move/zoom end so the chip does not flash after the first pan post-reload.
- **Map Inspector:** Text in the feature detail callout (attributes / description) can be selected and copied; the map canvas uses `user-select: none` for panning, which previously prevented selection inside the callout.
- **Map Inspector:** Feature detail callout stays open while panning the map (OpenLayers `move` is treated as a pan, so dismiss-on-click-outside no longer misfires when pointer-move events are not delivered during drag). The floating inspector window can be dragged partly off-screen (a 40px strip stays reachable to grab it again). The feature list is the only vertically scrolling region inside the inspector (the outer window body no longer scrolls as a whole). The list uses `overflow-x: hidden` and tighter row/map-head layout so a horizontal scrollbar does not appear.
- **Fix:** The feature list had collapsed to zero height (`flex: 1 1 0` inside an auto-sized column). The list now uses `flex: 1 1 auto`, a minimum height, and a `max-height` cap so rows stay visible and scroll inside the list. Un-minimizing the inspector restores the window body with `display: flex` (not `block`) so the column layout keeps working.
- **Map Inspector / ESRI_FEATURE:** Hover and selection no longer change **whole** FeatureServer layer order (which felt like shifting the whole map stack). Inspector stacking is limited to overlay layers: for ESRI points, temporary **lift** vector layers draw a **cloned** symbol (same avatar circle style as the source) so that one feature reads on top of other overlays; white halos sit under the rings; `requestAnimationFrame` re-pins overlays after new layers attach. Global ESRI_FEATURE vs WME POI stacking is still only what `syncOpenMapsLayerIndices` applies (not per-hover).
- **Map Inspector / WMS & WFS:** Rows that only have stored geometry (no live ESRI vector feature ref) now use the same avatar-colored point lift/halo/ring and the same line/polygon outline styling as ESRI_FEATURE highlights, driven from the row’s map title color.
- **Map Inspector:** Those geometry-only symbols stay on the map whenever the inspector window is open (subdued line/polygon styling; points match list avatar circles). Hover/selection overlays still draw on top; closing the inspector clears the persistent symbols.
- **Map Inspector:** Pointer hover and map click use the same top-down vector hit-testing as ESRI_FEATURE layers for those geometry-only symbols (including a pixel-radius fallback for small points).
- **Map Inspector:** Map clicks for inspector symbols and ESRI_FEATURE points are handled in **document capture** phase (when the pointer is over the map canvas) so WME **Places** and similar overlays that sit above the map in the DOM no longer eat the click before OpenLayers runs.
- **Map Inspector / stacking:** Inspector highlights, viewport-geometry symbols, and ESRI_FEATURE vectors are pinned in **one** OpenLayers pass (frontmost: rings/halos/lifts → persistent geom → each ESRI bbox then main). An `addlayer` hook re-pins after WME adds layers (e.g. Places) so symbols stay **drawn** above those overlays, not only hit-tested.
- **Map Inspector / Places:** After pinning, the script sets **CSS `z-index`** on those OpenLayers layer `div`s (and **mirrors** it on `canvas` / `svg` under the div with `!important` where needed). Values are assigned **from 2147483647 downward** (one step per layer in the ordered stack) so the **backmost** layer — the main ESRI_FEATURE vector with all default symbols — is **not** stuck at “`base` + 1” while WME Places uses a z-index **between** that and the inspector lift/halo layers (which made hover/selection clones look fine but left normal symbols visually under Places). The overlay stack is re-pinned after FeatureServer features load so stacking survives redraws.
- **Map Inspector / Places (WME layer refs):** `olMap.layers.indexOf(handle.layer)` can be **−1** when WME wraps or replaces the `OpenLayers.Layer` instance. The script now resolves layers by **`layer.name`** before `setLayerIndex` and before applying `z-index`, so pinning and styling hit the **live** map layer (otherwise changes had no visible effect while inspector-only layers still worked).
- **Map Inspector / Places (ESRI_FEATURE):** FeatureServer vector layers no longer use `map.title` as the OpenLayers `layer.name` (duplicate titles across catalog rows made name-based resolution pick the wrong layer). Each ESRI_FEATURE layer now uses a unique name `OpenMaps_ESRI_FEATURE_<map id>` and `openMapsMapId` so idle symbols receive the same high `z-index` pinning as inspector overlays (above WME Places).
- **Map Inspector / Places (stacking):** OpenLayers 2 sets `layer.div.style.zIndex` without `!important` in `setZIndex` / `resetLayersZIndex`, which overwrote our pinned overlay z-order after redraw or layer reorder—idle ESRI symbols could sit under WME Places while inspector-only layers still looked correct. The script now hooks `OpenLayers.Layer.prototype.setZIndex` and `map.resetLayersZIndex` to re-apply the overlay `!important` z-index values immediately after OL resets them.
- **Map Inspector / Places (stacking, v2026.04.03.18):** Overlay z-order is applied via **`!important` rules in an injected stylesheet** on `.openmaps-ol-overlay-z[data-openmaps-ol-ztok="…"]` (and matching `canvas`/`svg` descendants). That survives OpenLayers assigning plain inline `z-index` (author `!important` in a stylesheet outranks non-important inline). `OpenLayers.Map.prototype.resetLayersZIndex` is hooked as well as the live map instance, and reapplies only for `W.map.getOLMap()` so other OL maps on the page do not rewrite the shared rule block.
- **Map Inspector / Places (stacking, v2026.04.03.19):** Pinning and z-index styling now use **only layers present on `olMap.layers`**, then **sweep** the map for any `OpenMaps_ESRI_FEATURE_*` vector (and OpenMaps bbox vectors marked with `openMapsBboxMapId`) missing from that resolved list. Falling back to the handle’s layer when `indexOf` was −1 caused **`setLayerIndex` to no-op** and stylesheet hooks to target a **stale `div`**, while idle points kept drawing on WME’s live layer — matching “selected/hover OK, idle under Places.” **Google Places** sits above venue fills because WME already orders that native layer higher; it is not the same failure mode as our stale handle ref.
- **Map Inspector / Places + multi-ESRI (v2026.04.03.20):** Map hover/click no longer maps `hit.layer` to a catalog row with `h.layer === hit.layer` (breaks when WME swaps the OpenLayers.Vector instance). Uses `openMapsMapId`, `OpenMaps_ESRI_FEATURE_<id>`, and `openMapsResolveLayerOnOlMap` so stacked symbols from different FeatureServer maps don’t thrash. Swept overlay layers sort by **Active Maps** order so pins don’t reshuffle relative ESRI order every frame. Overlay layer `div`s that are direct children of `viewPortDiv` are **moved to the end** for paint-order tie-breaks; stylesheet rules are prefixed with **`#<olMap.div.id>`** when available. **`moveend`** triggers a debounced re-pin after pan.
- **Map Inspector / Places (v2026.04.03.21):** Pinned OpenMaps/inspector/ESRI overlay layers use **`pointer-events: none`** on the layer `div` and nested `canvas`/`svg`. They still paint above WME Places, but no longer steal the DOM hit target from Places (sibling layer divs do not receive events from another branch’s bubble path). FeatureServer picks still use **document capture** + map-pixel hit-testing. Reduces “Places unselectable until pan” after pointer leaves the map or WME toggles selection.

- **SDK / bootstrap (v2026.04.03.22):** Binds the official WME SDK via `getWmeSdk` (stable GreasyFork script id), registers the sidebar with `Sidebar.registerScriptTab` when possible, listens for map pan/zoom through SDK `Events` with OpenLayers fallbacks, toggles satellite imagery through `Map.setLayerVisibility` when supported, caps the OpenLayers readiness poll (~90s) with a clear console message, and uses Bootstrap 5 tooltips instead of jQuery. Documented polyfills remain for OpenLayers z-index stacking and `GM_xmlhttpRequest` / `unsafeWindow` where CSP or the Tampermonkey sandbox requires them.
- **Structure / maintenance (v2026.04.03.23):** Short region map comment after the Tampermonkey header; `//#region OpenMapsSdkBootstrap` wraps SDK helpers, OpenLayers readiness polling, and the start of `onWmeReady` through the SDK bind/log block (translations and the rest of the script stay outside for mergeability); `//#region OpenMapsBoot` wraps `onWmeInitialized`, `bootstrap`, and the entry call. No behavior change.

### 2026.04.02

- Edit panel: show a WMS Map Inspector backend tag so editors know which viewport feature requests will be used (ArcGIS REST vs GeoServer WFS). Displayed compactly as an extra chip right after the `Type` chip.
- **ESRI_FEATURE** (ArcGIS FeatureServer vectors): point markers match the Map Inspector list avatar color and are sized to **130% of that 16px list dot** (not the 32px active-map badge), drawn as native OpenLayers circles with a thin white rim. Highlight uses a ~95% opaque white halo **under** each highlighted symbol, with the active FeatureServer layer (and ring) stacked above other ESRI layers while highlighted; the highlighted feature is moved to the end of its vector layer so it draws above siblings (no hidden “lift” clone that could leave markers invisible after un-hover). **Map Inspector** keeps **selection** and **hover** highlights separate (both can show at once): selection stacks above hover on the map; the list uses `openmaps-inspector-list-row--sel` and `openmaps-inspector-list-row--hov`, with map hover syncing to the matching row when the pointer is not over the list. ESRI halos only show while an item is selected or hovered, render **under** point symbols (including with two active FeatureServer layers), and use a **white** hover ring (no blue outline). Closing the map callout clears selection on **click** outside (not when **dragging** to pan the map). Halo layer order is corrected after OpenLayers reorders so halos stay under point symbols. Map Inspector **re-links** in-memory vector rows after pan / ESRI_FEATURE refresh so the **selected symbol** keeps its highlight when the layer replaces features. Map hover uses a ~14px pixel-radius fallback when direct hit-testing misses small points; clicking a point opens Map Inspector if needed and selects like the list. ESRI_FEATURE layers stay above WME POI overlays so symbols remain visible.

### 2026.04.01

- Add ArcGIS Online WH **FeatureServer** point overlays: [World_Heritage_Sites](https://www.arcgis.com/apps/mapviewer/index.html?url=https://services7.arcgis.com/iEMmryaM5E3wkdnU/ArcGIS/rest/services/World_Heritage_Sites/FeatureServer&source=sd), [World_Heritage_UNESCO](https://www.arcgis.com/apps/mapviewer/index.html?url=https://services7.arcgis.com/iEMmryaM5E3wkdnU/ArcGIS/rest/services/World_Heritage_UNESCO/FeatureServer&source=sd) (both separate from the older `UNESCO/` Sites Navigator service).
- **ESRI_FEATURE** layers: geometry parsing now calls the shared `openMapsEsriGeometryToOpenLayers` helper (the overlay had still referenced the old in-inspector-only function, so features never appeared). FeatureServer responses also use a generation counter so slower requests cannot overwrite the map after a newer pan/zoom.
- **Map Inspector:** per-map checkbox now toggles overlay visibility like the Active Maps eye icon; row count next to each map title; per-map **⋮** menu with “Open data table” as the first action; optional skip of full viewport rescans when zoom and view center stay in the same bucket (Refresh forces a full run); detail callout stays open when panning the map; callout width tracks the inspector window at 110%; removed the experimental low-zoom WME sidebar “unlock” (footer toggle and injected styles).

### 2026.03.30

- WMS maps can set `wmsMinEffectiveZoom` (or `minEffectiveZoom`) so tile `GetMap` requests use at least that WME zoom level’s ground resolution when the user is zoomed farther out—more tiles when zoomed out, but friendlier to servers with tight `MaxScaleDenominator` rules. ČÚZK Katastrální mapa enables this at zoom 16 alongside `zoomRange` 16–22.
- When `zoomRange[0]` is set, WMS/XYZ/ESRI overlays skip remote tile URLs below that zoom (local transparent 1×1 instead) so `wmsMinEffectiveZoom` does not trigger server traffic outside the documented band.

### 2026.03.29

- Fix crash when the WMS server layer catalog finished loading while every sub-layer was toggled off (`mergeNewParams` on a missing OpenLayers layer).
- ČÚZK Katastrální mapa: `zoomRange` 16–22 so the “may not display at this zoom” hint matches ČÚZK parcel WMS scale limits and caps native tile resolution consistently.

## Acknowledgements

This project exists entirely thanks to the phenomenal foundational work of **Tom 'Glodenox' Puttemans**. The original WME OpenMaps script is a massive contribution to the global Waze editing community. This "remix" is simply a humble continuation  aimed at keeping the tool fast, stable and visually integrated with the modern editor.
